I am thinking about Cheryl.[p]
Even if she is held prisoner somewhere in this hospital, there is no guarantee that I can rescue her. [p]
In fact, there is no reason that the staircase I am descending should lead me to Cheryl.[p]
I begin to think that all of my current actions are all meaningless.[p]
However, generally speaking, since I arrived in Silent Hill, no, since the day before leaving for Silent Hill, no, even longer ago, [p]
since the day I met Cheryl, perhaps I have had no choice in my actions, that they have been determined by the someone's will.[p]
As I continue to the base of the stairs, I contemplate, what if my "life" up to this point had just been on one track?[p]
As I descend the stairs, my ears began ringing again. [p]
The ringing is so forceful that it cannot even be compared to before, and it forces me to squat down.[p]
What in the world has happened?[p]
Perhaps I have opened a door to hell, a door that should never be opened.[p]
Something is clearly changing, and it is for the worse.[p]
Going back will not be permitted.[p]
I must move forward. Forward.[p]
I put my hands together on my head, and then squeeze my temples tightly by using my elbows.[p]
The ringing then begins to sound like a demon is whispering in my ears; however, it doesn't stop.[p]
I blindly begin to run.[p]
Even if I am to die in this mad land, I must save my beloved Cheryl first. [p]
Believing that the answers are beyond the door, I know that I must discover at least one clue.[p]


