Several overlapping square figures are shaking in time with the sound of my heart.[p]
It is the wall at the end of the area.[p]
Another wall is lies perpendicular to it. [p]
There is a door present on this wall with a plate on it that says "Storehouse".[p]
Some chemicals have been placed on the table that is next to the door. [p]
There are three beakers of different sizes and a test tube.[p]
The test tube contains a liquid that is of a different color to that which is in the left-most beaker.[p]
I found a memo.[p]
"To create it you must come up with one deciliter of liquid and pour it into the test tube. [p]
No more or no less, that man had said.[p]
But there are no graduations on the beakers. [p]
This makes it impossible to come up with one deciliter using these three large beakers."[p]
Using the 10 deciliter, 7 deciliter, and 5 deciliter beakers you must create an amount of exactly one deciliter.[p]


